<p>Samuel taught us how to cooperate on a git project. Iâve worked a lot with git alone, keeping track of the development of my <a href="https://github.com/Jay-uu/pangenome-pipeline">Nextflow pipeline</a>. Working together with others in parallel was new, and a good exercise to get more familiar with the local repo, the staging area, the branches and the remote repo.</p>
